1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:12,500
Between two kingdoms — Vijaygarh and Naugarh — lived a love that no border could contain. Every star tonight reminds me of him… my Virendra. One day, Chandrakanta — I shall cross a hundred obstacles to reach you.

2
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:30,500
Princess — a scroll for you, sealed in Naugarh red. My tongue is quicker than a sparrow, my feet quicker still. Bless you, Tejsingh. Tell my prince I read every word twice… and dream them a third time. The aiyars — masters of disguise — carried love and secrets across enemy walls.

3
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:45,500
The path was a tilism — an enchantment of shifting stones, dart-flowers and clockwork guardians. For Chandrakanta — I shall bend even magic to my will! This way, prince! The mechanical peacock strikes on every third breath — count carefully!

4
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:58,500
You truly came. Through fire, through magic, through fear… For you, I would cross a thousand tilisms — and a thousand more. And so love — braver than any spy and older than any enchantment — wrote its own ending.
